# Sky culture name
msgid "Arabic (Al-Sufi)"
msgstr "ГЃrabe (Al-Sufi)"

# Sky culture introduction section in markdown format
msgid ""
"The Book of Fixed Stars was written shortly before 964 AD. Dr. Paul "
"Kunitzsch described it as \"the most outstanding among the works of the "
"prominent astronomer Abu 'l-бё¤usayn 'Abd al-RaбёҐmДЃn ibn 'Umar al-ЕћЕ«fi (born in "
"Rayy, 903; died 986), referred to as al-Sufi. In it, al-ЕћЕ«fД« treats the 48 "
"classical constellations, which were established and transmitted in "
"Ptolemy's Almagest. The description of each constellation comprises the "
"following four sections: first, a general discussion of the constellation "
"and its individual stars; this section also includes alЕћЕ«fi's criticism of "
"the Ptolemaic tradition and notices of his own observations. Second, a "
"record of the indigenous Arabic star names falling under that constellation, "
"and the exact identification of the respective stars with the corresponding "
"Ptolemaic stars. Third, two drawings of the constellation, one as it is seen "
"on a celestial globe, and the other one as it is seen in the sky. Fourth, a "
"table of the stars making up that constellation, giving a verbal description "
"of each star's location and its longitude, latitude, and magnitude. This "
"table closely follows the arrangement of Ptolemy's star catalogue in the "
"Almagest.\" [#1]. In addition to the four sections of each constellation "
"mentioned by dr. Kunitzsch, Al-Sufi would identify stars within the 6 "
"magnitudes that were neglected by Ptolemy, but he did not catalogue them and "
"was faithful to Ptolemy star catalog."
msgstr ""
"El Libro de las estrellas fijas se escribiГі poco antes del 964 d.C. El\n"
"Dr. Paul Kunitzsch lo describiГі como \"el mГЎs destacado entre los trabajos\n"
"del destacado astrГіnomo Abu 'l-бё¤usayn' Abd al-RaбёҐmДЃn ibn 'Umar al-ЕћЕ«fi\n"
"(nacido en Rayy, 903; muerto en 986), conocido como al- Sufi. En Г©l, al-"
"ЕћЕ«fД«\n"
"trata las 48 constelaciones clГЎsicas, que fueron establecidas y "
"transmitidas\n"
"en el Almagesto de Ptolomeo. La descripciГіn de cada constelaciГіn comprende\n"
"las siguientes cuatro secciones: primero, una discusiГіn general de la\n"
"constelaciГіn y sus estrellas individuales; esta secciГіn tambiГ©n incluye la\n"
"crГ­tica de alЕћЕ«fi de la tradiciГіn ptolemaica y notas de sus propias\n"
"observaciones. En segundo lugar, un registro de los nombres de las "
"estrellas\n"
"ГЎrabes indГ­genas que caen bajo esa constelaciГіn, y la identificaciГіn exacta\n"
"de las respectivas estrellas con las estrellas ptolemaicas\n"
"correspondientes. En tercer lugar, dos dibujos de la constelaciГіn , uno "
"como\n"
"se ve en un globo celeste, y el otro como se ve en el cielo. Cuarto, una\n"
"tabla de las estrellas que componen esa constelaciГіn, dando una descripciГіn\n"
"verbal de la ubicaciГіn de cada estrella y su longitud, latitud y\n"
"magnitud. Esta tabla sigue de cerca la disposiciГіn del catГЎlogo de "
"estrellas\n"
"de Ptolomeo en el Almagesto\". [#1]. AdemГЎs de las cuatro secciones de cada\n"
"constelaciГіn mencionadas por el dr. Kunitzsch, Al-Sufi identificarГ­a\n"
"estrellas dentro de las 6 magnitudes que fueron ignoradas por Ptolomeo, "
"pero\n"
"no las catalogГі y fue fiel al catГЎlogo de estrellas de Ptolomeo."

# Sky culture description section in markdown format
msgid ""
"An important aspect of the general discussion section is Al-Sufi method of "
"facilitating the star identification. He describes each individual star in "
"more than way: By the star position related to the constellation figure, by "
"its magnitude, by the asterism it forms with other stars like triangle or "
"arc shapes, sometimes by the star position related to the Milky way, and by "
"the angular distance from a close by star. I have counted more than 700 "
"angular distances measured by al-Sufi in his book. The units he uses for "
"angular distances are cubits, spear length, man-height, span, and finger. Al-"
"Sufi explicitly said in his book that a cubit is equal to two degrees and 20 "
"minutes [#2]. For the other units, Schjellerup concluded some values, but "
"tracking the 700 measurements, I came up with different values. The "
"following table summarizes the units and relationship to the cubit value "
"from Schjellerup[#3] and from my research.\n"
"\n"
"### Angular distance units used by Al-Sufi\n"
"\n"
"<table>\n"
"<tr valign=\"top\">\n"
"\t<td><notr>&nbsp;</notr></td>\n"
"\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"><b>Schjellerup</b></td>\n"
"\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"><b>Khalid</b></td>\n"
"</tr>\n"
"<tr valign=\"top\">\n"
"\t<td><b>unit</b></td>\n"
"\t<td><b>cubits</b></td>\n"
"\t<td><b>Angular Value</b></td>\n"
"\t<td><b>cubits</b></td>\n"
"\t<td><b>Angular Value</b></td>\n"
"</tr>\n"
"<tr valign=\"top\">\n"
"\t<td>spear</td>\n"
"\t<td>6 cubits</td>\n"
"\t<td><notr>14В°</notr></td>\n"
"\t<td>6 cubits</td>\n"
"\t<td><notr>14В°</notr></td>\n"
"</tr>\n"
"<tr valign=\"top\">\n"
"\t<td>Man-Height</td>\n"
"\t<td></td>\n"
"\t<td></td>\n"
"\t<td>3 cubits</td>\n"
"\t<td><notr>7В°</notr></td>\n"
"</tr>\n"
"<tr valign=\"top\">\n"
"\t<td>cubit</td>\n"
"\t<td>1 cubit</td>\n"
"\t<td><notr>2В°20'</notr></td>\n"
"\t<td>1 cubit</td>\n"
"\t<td><notr>2В°20'</notr></td>\n"
"</tr>\n"
"<tr valign=\"top\">\n"
"\t<td>span</td>\n"
"\t<td>1/3 of a cubit</td>\n"
"\t<td><notr>47'</notr></td>\n"
"\t<td>1/2 of a cubit</td>\n"
"\t<td><notr>1В°10'</notr></td>\n"
"</tr>\n"
"<tr valign=\"top\">\n"
"\t<td>finger</td>\n"
"\t<td>1/32 of a cubit</td>\n"
"\t<td><notr>4.4'</notr></td>\n"
"\t<td>1/16 of a cubit</td>\n"
"\t<td><notr>8.75'</notr></td>\n"
"</tr>\n"
"</table>\n"
"\n"
"Another important aspect of Al-Sufi book is his record of the indigenous "
"Arabic star names falling under each constellation, and the exact "
"identification of the respective stars with the corresponding Ptolemaic "
"stars. This means that we are looking at two layers of stars knowledge at "
"the same time: the Ptolemaic one and the indigenous Arab one.\n"
"\n"
"### The Sky Culture\n"
"\n"
"This sky culture is a result of a research done on several manuscripts of "
"the book, oldest of which is the [#8].\n"
"\n"
"First, the manuscripts of the Book of Fixed Stars were critically edited, "
"and the text was produced. Second, each member star of the 48 constellations "
"was identified according to Al-Sufi description, and new tables were built "
"including modern star designations from the Hipparcos, Bright stars, and "
"Bayer catalogues. Third, Arab indigenous star names were collected and "
"identified as mapped by Al-Sufi to the Ptolemaic ones. All the previous "
"steps were included in a book published digitally of the Book of Fixed Stars "
"plus explanations and commentary by Khalid Al-Ajaji[#4].\n"
"\n"
"The sky culture stick figures of the constellations are the images in the "
"Ulugh Beg manuscript of the Book of Fixed Stars, extracted, and adapted for "
"Stellarium by Mr. Kutaibaa Akraa [#5]. The star names file includes the star "
"number in the constellation as the primary star name and the description of "
"the star in the tables as a secondary name. For example, Polaris primary "
"name that is displayed with the star is: UMi1, UMi being Ursa Minor and 1 is "
"the first star of this constellation. If the star is selected other "
"secondary names are displayed, which will display \"The star on the end of "
"the tail\" on the top of the screen. The constellation lines are constructed "
"according to the constellation shapes with an attempt to include most of the "
"member stars. For indigenous Arab star knowledge, individual star names were "
"added to the star file as secondary names, while names of group of stars "
"were defined through asterism names and asterism lines files.\n"
"\n"
"The translation of star descriptions from Arabic into English was extracted "
"from Ernie Wright website[#6] which was transcribed from Toomer's "
"translation of the Almagest[#7]. The translation was modified in a few "
"places to agree with Al-Sufi wording.\n"
"\n"
"The single source of the sky culture is the Book of Fixed Stars and the "
"objective is to give a faithful representation of the book content."
msgstr ""
"Un aspecto importante de la secciГіn de discusiГіn general es el mГ©todo de\n"
"Al-Sufi para facilitar la identificaciГіn de estrellas. Describe cada\n"
"estrella individual de mГЎs de una manera: por la posiciГіn de la estrella\n"
"relacionada con la figura de la constelaciГіn, por su magnitud, por el\n"
"asterismo que forma con otras estrellas como formas de triГЎngulo o arco, a\n"
"veces por la posiciГіn de la estrella relacionada con la VГ­a LГЎctea, y por "
"la\n"
"distancia angular de una estrella cercana. He contado mГЎs de 700 distancias\n"
"angulares medidas por al-Sufi en su libro. Las unidades que usa para las\n"
"distancias angulares son codos, longitud de la lanza, altura del hombre,\n"
"envergadura y dedo. Al-Sufi dijo explГ­citamente en su libro que un codo es\n"
"igual a dos grados y 20 minutos [#2]. Para las otras unidades, Schjellerup\n"
"concluyГі algunos valores, pero al rastrear las 700 mediciones, obtuve\n"
"valores diferentes. La siguiente tabla resume las unidades y la relaciГіn "
"con\n"
"el valor del codo de Schjellerup[#3] y\n"
"de mi investigaciГіn.\n"
"\n"
"### Unidades de distancia angular utilizadas por Al-Sufi\n"
"\n"
"<table>\n"
"<tr valign=\"top\">\n"
"\t<td>&nbsp;</td>\n"
"\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"><b>Schjellerup</b></td>\n"
"\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"><b>Khalid</b></td>\n"
"</tr>\n"
"<tr valign=\"top\">\n"
"\t<td><b>unidad</b></td>\n"
"\t<td><b>codos</b></td>\n"
"\t<td><b>Valor Angular</b></td>\n"
"\t<td><b>codos</b></td>\n"
"\t<td><b>Valor Angular</b></td>\n"
"</tr>\n"
"<tr valign=\"top\">\n"
"\t<td>lanza</td>\n"
"\t<td>6 codos</td>\n"
"\t<td>14В°</td>\n"
"\t<td>6 codos</td>\n"
"\t<td>14В°</td>\n"
"</tr>\n"
"<tr valign=\"top\">\n"
"\t<td>Altura del hombre</td>\n"
"\t<td></td>\n"
"\t<td></td>\n"
"\t<td>3 codos</td>\n"
"\t<td>7В°</td>\n"
"</tr>\n"
"<tr valign=\"top\">\n"
"\t<td>codo</td>\n"
"\t<td>1 codo</td>\n"
"\t<td>2В°20'</td>\n"
"\t<td>1 codo</td>\n"
"\t<td>2В°20'</td>\n"
"</tr>\n"
"<tr valign=\"top\">\n"
"\t<td>envergadura</td>\n"
"\t<td>1/3 de un codo</td>\n"
"\t<td>47'</td>\n"
"\t<td>1/2 de un codo</td>\n"
"\t<td>1В°10'</td>\n"
"</tr>\n"
"<tr valign=\"top\">\n"
"\t<td>dedo</td>\n"
"\t<td>1/32 de un codo</td>\n"
"\t<td>4.4'</td>\n"
"\t<td>1/16 de un codo</td>\n"
"\t<td>8.75'</td>\n"
"</tr>\n"
"</table>\n"
"\n"
"Otro aspecto importante del libro de Al-Sufi es su registro de los nombres\n"
"de las estrellas ГЎrabes indГ­genas que caen bajo cada constelaciГіn, y la\n"
"identificaciГіn exacta de las respectivas estrellas con las correspondientes\n"
"estrellas ptolemaicas. Esto significa que estamos viendo dos capas de\n"
"conocimiento de las estrellas al mismo tiempo: la ptolemaica y la ГЎrabe\n"
"indГ­gena.\n"
"\n"
"### La Cultura Estelar\n"
"\n"
"Esta cultura estelar es el resultado de una investigaciГіn realizada en\n"
"varios manuscritos del libro, el mГЎs antiguo de los cuales es la [#8].\n"
"\n"
"Primero, se editaron crГ­ticamente los manuscritos del Libro de las "
"estrellas\n"
"fijas y se produjo el texto. En segundo lugar, cada estrella miembro de las\n"
"48 constelaciones se identificГі de acuerdo con la descripciГіn de Al-Sufi, y\n"
"se construyeron tablas nuevas que incluГ­an designaciones de estrellas\n"
"modernas de los catГЎlogos de Hipparcos, Bright stars y Bayer. En tercer\n"
"lugar, los nombres de las estrellas indГ­genas ГЎrabes se recopilaron e\n"
"identificaron como asignados por Al-Sufi a los ptolemaicos. Todos los pasos\n"
"anteriores se incluyeron en un libro publicado digitalmente del Libro de\n"
"estrellas fijas mГЎs explicaciones y comentarios de Khalid Al-Ajaji[#4].\n"
"\n"
"Las figuras de palo de las culturas estelares de las constelaciones son las\n"
"imГЎgenes del manuscrito Ulugh Beg del Libro de las estrellas fijas,\n"
"extraГ­das y adaptadas para Stellarium por el Sr. Kutaibaa Akraa[#5]. El "
"archivo de nombres de estrellas incluye\n"
"el nГєmero de estrella en la constelaciГіn como nombre de estrella principal "
"y\n"
"la descripciГіn de la estrella en las tablas como nombre secundario. Por\n"
"ejemplo, el nombre principal de Polaris que se muestra con la estrella es:\n"
"UMi1, UMi es Ursa Minor y 1 es la primera estrella de esta constelaciГіn. Si\n"
"se selecciona la estrella, se muestran otros nombres secundarios, que\n"
"mostrarГЎn \"La estrella al final de la cola\" en la parte superior de la\n"
"pantalla. Las lГ­neas de la constelaciГіn se construyen de acuerdo con las\n"
"formas de la constelaciГіn con un intento de incluir la mayorГ­a de las\n"
"estrellas miembros. Para el conocimiento de las estrellas ГЎrabes indГ­genas,\n"
"los nombres de estrellas individuales se agregaron al archivo de estrellas\n"
"como nombres secundarios, mientras que los nombres de grupos de estrellas "
"se\n"
"definieron a travГ©s de nombres de asterismo y archivos de lГ­neas de\n"
"asterismo.\n"
"\n"
"La traducciГіn de las descripciones de las estrellas del ГЎrabe al inglГ©s se\n"
"extrajo del sitio web de Ernie Wright[#6], que fue transcrito de la "
"traducciГіn de\n"
"Toomer del Almagesto[#7]. La traducciГіn\n"
"fue modificada en algunos lugares para estar de acuerdo con la redacciГіn de\n"
"Al-Sufi.\n"
"\n"
"La Гєnica fuente de la cultura estelar es el Libro de Estrellas Fijas y el\n"
"objetivo es dar una representaciГіn fiel del contenido del libro."

